  "text": "Once upon a matchday — it was the round of 16, on the 7th of July 2026 — two teams walked out under the soft evening lights. Belgium ended the USA's home World Cup with a clinical, four-goal display. The hosts dreamed of a deep run in front of their own fans; Belgium's golden-tinged generation had other ideas.\n\nFirst, in the 9th minute, Charles De Ketelaere made it 0–1; then, in the 31st minute, Malik Tillman made it 1–1; then, in the 33rd minute, Charles De Ketelaere made it 1–2; then, in the 57th minute, Hans Vanaken made it 1–3; and at last, in the 93rd minute, Romelu Lukaku made it 1–4.\n\nCharles De Ketelaere's first-half double did the early damage, either side of Malik Tillman's fine reply for the hosts. For a moment, at 2-1, the American crowd believed a comeback was on. Hans Vanaken's composed finish and a late Romelu Lukaku strike snuffed that out and made the scoreline emphatic. Belgium looked ruthless and experienced — the profile of a side that intends to be around in the final week.\n\nThe crowd hummed like a distant sea, rising and falling with every chance.\n\nAnd so the story ended USA 1–4 Belgium. Belgium carried on their long journey, and USA lay down to rest. Every goal in this tale is a true one — kept safe and provable on the blockchain by TxLINE — so you can close your eyes knowing not a single fact was ever made up. Sleep well, and goodnight.",
